Here are standalone Console/CLI steps for S3 cleanup—no script needed. Copy-paste commands.

Prerequisites (Console/CLI)
1. Create Inventory Bucket (Console: S3 > Create bucket; CLI):

text
aws s3 mb s3://your-unique-cleanup-inventory-$(date +%s) --region us-east-1
export INV_BUCKET=your-unique-cleanup-inventory-123
2. Create Batch Ops IAM Role (Console: IAM > Create role > S3 > Batch Operations):

Name: S3BatchCleanupRole

Policy: Custom with s3:DeleteObject, s3:GetObject* on *

Export ARN:

text
export BATCH_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::$(aws sts get-caller-identity --query Account --output text):role/S3BatchCleanupRole
Step 1: Enable S3 Inventory on Matching Buckets (Console/CLI, 5 mins)
Find buckets:

text
aws s3api list-buckets --query "Buckets[?contains(Name, \`access-logs\`) || contains(Name, \`athena-logs\`)].Name" --output table
Console (per bucket):

S3 > [bucket] > Management > Inventory configurations > Create.

Id: cleanup-inv-1

Status: Enabled

Frequency: Weekly

Report: Parquet, Optional: Size/LastModifiedDate/StorageClass/ETag

Destination: $INV_BUCKET (arn:aws:s3:::$INV_BUCKET/inventory)

CLI (loop):

text
for bucket in $(aws s3api list-buckets --query "Buckets[?contains(Name, \`access-logs\`) || contains(Name, \`athena-logs\`)].Name[]" --output text); do
  aws s3api put-bucket-inventory-configuration --bucket $bucket --inventory-configuration '{
    "Id": "cleanup-inv-1",
    "IsEnabled": true,
    "Destination": {"S3BucketDestination": {"AccountId": "'$(aws sts get-caller-identity --query Account --output text)'", "Format": "Parquet", "Bucket": "arn:aws:s3:::'$INV_BUCKET'"}},
    "Schedule": {"Frequency": "Weekly"},
    "IncludedObjectVersions": "Current",
    "OptionalFields": ["Size", "LastModifiedDate", "StorageClass"]
  }'
done
Wait: 24-48h. Verify: aws s3 ls $INV_BUCKET/inventory/ --recursive

Step 2: Setup Athena Table (Console/CLI, 5 mins)
Console:

Athena > Query editor > New DB: s3_cleanup.

Validation query:

text
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE IF NOT EXISTS s3_cleanup.s3_inventory (
  bucket string, key string, versionId string, isLatest boolean, isDeleteMarker boolean,
  size bigint, lastModifiedDate bigint, eTag string, storageClass string,
  encryptionStatus string
)
PARTITIONED BY (configId string, reportDate string)
ROW FORMAT SERDE 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.parquet.serde.ParquetHiveSerDe'
LOCATION 's3://$INV_BUCKET/inventory/'
TBLPROPERTIES ('parquet.compress'='SNAPPY');
Run MSCK REPAIR TABLE s3_cleanup.s3_inventory;

CLI:

text
aws athena start-query-execution --query-string "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS s3_cleanup;"
aws athena start-query-execution --query-string "CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE ... " --query-execution-context Database=s3_cleanup --result-configuration OutputLocation=s3://$INV_BUCKET/athena/
aws athena start-query-execution --query-string "MSCK REPAIR TABLE s3_cleanup.s3_inventory;" --query-execution-context Database=s3_cleanup
Verify: SELECT count(*) FROM s3_cleanup.s3_inventory LIMIT 10;

Step 3: Query & Export Manifest (Console, 10 mins)
Athena Query (adjust date):

text
SELECT bucket, key
FROM s3_cleanup.s3_inventory
WHERE (bucket LIKE '%access-logs%' OR bucket LIKE '%athena-logs%')
  AND storageClass = 'STANDARD'
  AND from_unixtime(lastModifiedDate/1000) < date('2025-09-01')
  AND isLatest = true AND isDeleteMarker = false
Run > Download CSV (rename columns to Bucket,Key; save as manifest.csv).

Upload: aws s3 cp manifest.csv s3://$INV_BUCKET/manifests/cleanup-manifest.csv
Count first: Add LIMIT 10 for test.

Step 4: Create Batch Delete Job (Console, 2 mins)
Console:

S3 > Management tab > Batch operations > Create job.

Manifest: CSV format > Browse s3://$INV_BUCKET/manifests/cleanup-manifest.csv

Operation: Delete objects (no Lambda).

IAM role: Select S3BatchCleanupRole.

Report: s3://$INV_BUCKET/batch-reports/ (CSV).

Priority: 10 (High).

Create > Monitor in Batch operations list.

CLI:

text
aws s3control create-job --account-id $(aws sts get-caller-identity --query Account --output text) \
  --operation '{"S3DeleteObject": {}}' \
  --manifest '{"Spec": {"Format": "S3BatchOperations_CSV_20180820", "Fields": ["Bucket","Key"]}, "Location": {"ObjectArn": "arn:aws:s3:::'$INV_BUCKET'/manifests/cleanup-manifest.csv", "ETag": "'$(aws s3api head-object --bucket $INV_BUCKET --key manifests/cleanup-manifest.csv --query ETag --output text)'"}}' \
  --report '{"Bucket": "arn:aws:s3:::'$INV_BUCKET'", "Format": "Report_CSV_20180820", "Enabled": true, "Prefix": "batch-reports/", "ReportScope": "AllTasks"}' \
  --priority 10 --role-arn $BATCH_ROLE_ARN
Monitor: S3 Console > Batch ops > Jobs.

Step 5: Monitor & Verify (Console)
Job status: S3 > Batch operations > [JobId] > Tasks (progress %).

Reports: aws s3 ls s3://$INV_BUCKET/batch-reports/JOB_ID/ --recursive

output.csv: Successes.

unprocessedmanifest.csv: Failures (retry if needed).

Cancel if test: Batch ops > Job > Cancel.

Test Flow: Step1 on 1 bucket > Step2-4 with LIMIT 10. Scales to 100M+ automatically.

